{
  "texts": [
    "This statement is proven in appendix A.",
    "There are two independent scalings here; one given by the stress tensor, where ξ α and η α both scale as weight 1/2 fields and one given by (2.2) where these fields scale oppositely.",
    "It is sufficient to impose Zn = 0 for n ≥ 0, since [Zm, Zn] = 0.",
    "It may appear that this six dimensional theory could stand in its own right, without the need for the four compact dimensions of M4.",
    "Unfortunately, the field content of the M4 sector is needed to construct a measure on the moduli space of Riemann Surfaces Mg,n that will cancel the anomaly from the ρ ghost current, as we will see in section 3.3."
  ]
}